{
  "AC": "Skill under skills/ that: (1) documents Samba/VFAT-safe rename rules with ':' sanitized; (2) gathers candidate names from cue/spec + musicology provider data; (3) resolves conflicts via most-common then least-verbose; (4) picks genre-appropriate conventions (collections / classical / pop-rock); (5) produces a rename plan for dirs and files. Agent can apply the skill when asked to correct FLAC directory names.",
  "ActualSummary": "Shipped skills/correct-flac-names: VFAT/Samba-safe renames, meta priority (combined\u2192johan\u2192online\u2192txt/cue), homogeneous The-stripped artist dirs with musicscan The-variants (in sibling bin), VA only for true comps, title denoise (year/encoding/edition out of dirname), multi-disc harmonize, collision DUP suffixes, and original-album-name in .meta.johan.json as stopgap until shadup path start/end (d2057c6f). Dry-ran plans to /tmp only; no flac/files renames applied.",
  "BaseSha": "66d10d039a7857db498f25c27451f3f7e9441146",
