    "raw": "create a skill that attempts to correct the naming of directory and its files to both be correct and to avoid characters / forms that do not conform to samba / vfat standard.  The sources of data will be contained cue and spec files, as well as results from musicology providers. If there are multiple conflicting answers, choose the most common one, or least verbose.  Recognize that collections and classical music and modern pop/rock all have different naming conventions and chose the name that most closely resembles the convetions.  But p0 requirement is the samba / vfat naming. notably ':' must be sanitized."
  },
